<paragraph blockId="16.[160,1156,142,237]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,307,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">Colouration.</emphasis>
Wings: bi-banded; light castaneous: scape, pedicel, mandible, palpi, wing venation, tibiae, and tarsi; orange: pronotum and mesonotum; castaneous: head, tegulae, coxae, trochanters, femora; dark castaneous: flagellum and metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[160,1156,281,653]" box="[160,262,281,307]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[160,1156,281,653]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moczar, 1970)" baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[453,759,316,341]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis box="[453,581,316,341]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">I. consimilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L" box="[597,751,316,341]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" pagination="175 - 203" refId="ref12220" refString="Moczar L. 1970. Mesitiinae of world with new genera and species. I. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zool Academ Sci Hung. 16: 175 - 203." type="journal article" year="1970">Móczár, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by having eye small, longitudinal sulcus of anteromesoscutum absent, and posterior projection of metapectal-propodeal complex short. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2020" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2020" box="[456,671,386,411]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shiraz" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[456,671,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">Incertosulcus shiraz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[681,772,386,411]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has body dark castaneous, head longer than wide, median clypeal lobe quadrate, ocelli very small, anteromesoscutum coriaceous, the notaulus narrow, the posterior carina of metapectal-propodeal complex incomplete medially, lateral surface of metapectal-propodeal complex without metapectal carina and mesopleural suture with inner margin strigate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[160,1156,281,653]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">
The metapectal-propodeal complex posterior carina incomplete medially is an interesting characteristic observed for this species and genus, because this characteristic was recorded only for 
<taxonomicName box="[363,589,628,653]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Heterocoelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[363,498,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378">Heterocoelia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berland" authorityYear="1928" box="[677,794,628,653]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mesitiinae">Mesitiinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
